    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at Deenanath Mangeshkar Hospital. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Radiologist to strengthen our Gwalior-based team.\n\nAbout Deenanath Mangeshkar Hospital:\nDeenanath Mangeshkar Hospital is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Diagnose and treat medical conditions following established protocols\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n• Provide high-quality patient care and maintain patient records\n• Respond to medical emergencies and provide immediate care\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• MBBS / MD / MS from recognized medical college\n• 1-3 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Patient Care\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in Medical Terminology\n• Proficiency in Surgical Procedures\n• Proficiency in Infection Control\n• Proficiency in NABH Standards\n• Proficiency in Clinical Documentation\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Provident Fund and Gratuity as per company policy\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Recognition and rewards programs\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Salary Range: 4 LPA - 9 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Gwalior, Madhya Pradesh, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Deenanath Mangeshkar Hospital!",
